&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;How does an Agent &amp;ldquo;see&amp;rdquo; the world?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It has no eyes, no ears—just an input window. No matter how complex the outside world is, an Agent can only perceive one thing: &lt;strong&gt;Context&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A prompt is context. A tool call&amp;rsquo;s return value is context. A file&amp;rsquo;s contents are context. An error message is context.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an Agent: &lt;strong&gt;Everything is context&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
